</form>

<p><strong>Menu Integration</strong>: XAMPP isn't in PortableApps.com Format, but it easily integrates with the PortableApps.com Suite by using the <a href="http://downloads.sourceforge.net/portableapps/XAMPP_1.4.paf.exe?download">XAMPP Launcher 1.4</a> and installing XAMPP in the root directory of your portable device (as recommended). You can open the self-extracting archive with <a href="/apps/utilities/7-zip_portable">7-Zip Portable</a> or download the larger ZIP archive.</p>

<p><a href="/donate"><img src="/files/images/buttons/donation_button.png" width="110" height="23" border="0" align="top" alt="Make a Donation" /></a> - Support PortableApps.com's development and hosting</p>

<h2>Features</h2>
<p><a href="/files/images/screenshots/xampp.png" rel="lightbox"><img width="200" height="150" align="right" alt="XAMPP Screenshot" src="/files/images/screenshots/xampp_small.png" class="screenshotthumbnail" /></a>XAMPP is a complete web, database and FTP server package for Windows that's ready to go in minutes and completely portable.  The full XAMPP package includes:</p>
<ul>
<li>Apache</li>
<li>MySQL</li>
<li>PHP + PEAR</li>
<li>MiniPerl</li>
<li>OpenSSL</li>
<li>phpMyAdmin</li>
<li>XAMPP Control Panel</li>
<li>Webalizer</li>
<li>Mercury Mail Transport System</li>
<li>FileZilla FTP Server</li>
<li>SQLite</li>
<li>ADODB</li>
<li>Zend Optimizer</li>
<li>XAMPP Security</li>
</ul>
<p><b>XAMPP Lite</b> leaves off the additional packages and sticks to Apache, mySQL, phpMyAdmin, SQLite and related packages resulting in an installation that's  significantly smaller.  There are no upgrade packages for XAMPP Lite like there are for XAMPP, though.</p>
<p><b>Add-Ons</b>: You can also add in Perl or Tomcat with the <a href="http://www.apachefriends.org/en/xampp-windows.html#644">XAMPP Add-Ons</a>.</p>
<h2><a name="support"></a>Support</h2>
<p>For help getting up and running, visit the
<a href="http://www.apachefriends.org/en/xampp-windows.html#641">XAMPP for Windows page</a>:</p>
<ul class="support-links">
<li><a href="http://www.apachefriends.org/en/xampp-windows.html#521">Installation without the Installer</a> (Use this for portable use)<br /><em>Note: Be sure not to run setup_xampp.bat, it is used for local installs</em></li><li><a href="http://www.apachefriends.org/en/xampp-windows.html#1173">Start, Stop &amp; Test XAMPP<br /></a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.apachefriends.org/en/xampp-windows.html#1221">The XAMPP Security Console</a> (Must Read)</li>
<li><a href="http://www.apachefriends.org/en/faq-xampp-windows.html">XAMPP for Windows FAQ</a></li>
</ul>
<p>You can also post a note in the <a href="http://www.apachefriends.org/f/">Apache Friends Support Forum</a>.</p>
